  "prompt": "Why do I feel more sleepy in evening 5pm-7pm?",
  "response": "Feeling sleepy between 5-7 PM is common and can be attributed to several factors:\n\n1. Circadian Rhythm\n- Natural dip in energy levels\n- Body's internal biological clock experiences a slight decrease in alertness\n- Often referred to as the \"afternoon slump\"\n\n2. Hormonal Changes\n- Decrease in cortisol levels\n- Rise in melatonin production\n- Signals body to prepare for sleep\n\n3. Blood Sugar Levels\n- Post-lunch blood sugar drop\n- Potential digestive processes slowing down metabolism\n\n4. Daily Energy Expenditure\n- Accumulation of daily physical and mental fatigue\n- Natural exhaustion from work or daily activities\n\n5. Potential Lifestyle Factors\n- Poor sleep quality the previous night\n- Insufficient nutrition\n- Lack of physical activity\n- Dehydration\n- High-carbohydrate lunch\n\n6. Potential Medical Conditions\n- Sleep disorders\n- Vitamin deficiencies\n- Anemia\n- Thyroid issues\n\nRecommended Solutions:\n- Maintain consistent sleep schedule\n- Regular exercise\n- Balanced diet\n- Stay hydrated\n- Short power nap (15-20 minutes)\n- Exposure to natural light\n- Manage stress levels\n\nIf persistent, consult healthcare professional.",
